      <h2>Ranking Methodology</h2>
      <p>
        Our analysis of the best uranium stocks utilizes a comprehensive methodology to balance upside potential with operational risk. The key factors considered include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Asset Quality:</strong> We prioritize companies holding high-grade ore, scalable resources, and low-cost extraction methods (like In-Situ Recovery or ISR).</li>
        <li><strong>Jurisdictional Safety:</strong> Projects located in mining-friendly, politically stable regions (e.g., Canada, United States, Australia) are heavily favored over those in high-risk geopolitics.</li>
        <li><strong>Time to Production:</strong> Current producers or near-term developers rank higher than early-stage explorers, as they can immediately capitalize on current high spot prices.</li>
        <li><strong>Balance Sheet & Management:</strong> Companies with fully funded CapEx programs and management teams with a proven history of actually building and operating mines receive premium rankings.</li>
        <li><strong>Contracting Strategy:</strong> We analyze how much production is locked into long-term utility contracts versus left unhedged to capture spot price spikes.</li>
      </ul>
