      <details>
        <summary>Why are uranium stocks going up?</summary>
        <p>
          Uranium stocks are rising due to a structural supply deficit, renewed global interest in nuclear energy as a clean baseload power source, and geopolitical supply chain concerns.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What is the best uranium ETF?</summary>
        <p>
          The Global X Uranium ETF (URA) is the largest and most liquid uranium ETF, offering broad exposure to miners and physical uranium trusts. The Sprott Uranium Miners ETF (URNM) is another popular choice.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Are uranium stocks a good long-term investment?</summary>
        <p>
