        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Which uranium company produces the most?</summary>
        <p>
          Kazatomprom (based in Kazakhstan) is the world's largest producer of uranium, while Cameco (based in Canada) is the second-largest and the largest publicly traded pure-play.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>How does physical uranium differ from uranium miners?</summary>
        <p>
          Physical uranium funds (like Sprott Physical Uranium Trust) buy and hold actual uranium. Their price tracks the spot commodity. Miners actually dig uranium out of the ground, meaning their stock price carries operational and execution risks alongside commodity price exposure.
        </p>
      </details>
